 LG bets big on audio 

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 LG Electronics product group head 

 (audio-video business) Sanjeev Jain (right) and vice-president 

 (marketing) Girish Bapat in New Delhi on Friday. Picture 

 by Prem Singh

 New Delhi, Sept. 9: LG Electronics India (LGEIL) today launched a range of audio systems, including the next-generation Karaoke. 

 While the audio sets are priced between Rs 8,000-Rs 20,000, the Karaoke range is available for Rs 30,000-50,000.

 The Korean consumer electronics company has a 10 per cent market share in the Rs 1,500-crore audio-video market. We have set a target to earn at least Rs 400 crore by next year, LGEIL product group head-audio video business Sanjeev Jain said. By next year, we will offer at least 21 products. We will attempt to strengthen our position in this segment, LGEIL vice-president-marketing Girish Bapat said. 




